## Task: Split Models/FileSystemModels.cs into per-DTO files
## Step: execute

### Models/FileSystemModels.cs
```cs
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace TestProject.Models;

public sealed record FileEntryDto(string Name, string Path, bool IsDirectory, long Size, System.DateTime LastModified, int ItemCount);

public sealed record BrowseResultDto(string Path, string? Parent, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Entries, int FolderCount, int FileCount, long TotalSize);

public sealed record SearchResultDto(string Query, string Path, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Results);

public sealed record MoveRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);

public sealed record CopyRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);

```
Split the flat `Models/FileSystemModels.cs` dumping ground (5 DTOs in one file) into focused per-DTO files. This resolves the name/file mismatch where the filename `FileSystemModels` doesn't describe any single type.

Create the following files under `Models/`, each containing exactly one type with its full XML doc comment (write fresh, concise doc comments — do NOT carry over temporal references):

1. `Models/FileEntryDto.cs` — `FileEntryDto` record.
2. `Models/BrowseResultDto.cs` — `BrowseResultDto` record.
3. `Models/SearchResultDto.cs` — `SearchResultDto` record.
4. `Models/MoveRequest.cs` — `MoveRequest` record.
5. `Models/CopyRequest.cs` — `CopyRequest` record.

All types stay in the `TestProject.Models` namespace. Delete `Models/FileSystemModels.cs` after creating the five files.

The existing record definitions are:
```csharp
